From 82999b1479db0a87297bede20fab60c51ad142b7 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Masahito S <firelzrd@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 10 Mar 2026 01:58:52 +0900
Subject: [PATCH] lib: add WAVL (Weak AVL) tree implementation with rbtree
 proxy headers

Add a complete WAVL tree library that mirrors the existing rbtree API.
WAVL trees are rank-balanced BSTs that guarantee at most 2 rotations
per insert/delete (amortized O(1) structural changes) while maintaining
O(log n) height, making them suitable for latency-sensitive paths such
as the scheduler.

The API surface mirrors rbtree exactly:
  - wavl_types.h: wavl_node, wavl_root, wavl_root_cached
  - wavl.h: wavl_link_node, wavl_insert_rebalance, wavl_erase,
    wavl_first/next/prev, wavl_add_cached, wavl_first_cached
  - wavl_augmented.h: wavl_augment_callbacks, wavl_add_augmented_cached,
    wavl_erase_augmented_cached, WAVL_DECLARE_CALLBACKS[_MAX]
  - lib/wavl.c: exported symbols for insert/erase rebalance, iteration

Additionally, three proxy headers (rbtree_wavl.h, rbtree_wavl_types.h,
rbtree_wavl_augmented.h) map rb_* names to wavl_* equivalents, allowing
existing code to switch to WAVL trees with zero code changes by simply
including rbtree_wavl_augmented.h instead of rbtree_augmented.h.
